ield hockey teamin 1980 in Moscow.\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1604, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999719429984, \"rank\": 2.7949581525824138e-08, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two-time African journalist of the year,Hopewell Chin'ono, took to X, formerly Twitter, topost to his nearly 750 000 followersthat: \\\"The world media is once again having a laugh at the expense of Zimbabwe after it sent 67 officials to the Paris Olympics and only 7 athletes.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.590680538299251e-24, \"text\": \"Zimbabwe\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The officials include the country's Vice President, General Constantino Chiwenga, his wife, and the country's sports minister, Kirsty Coventry.\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constantine_Chiwenga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Constantino Chiwenga\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constantine_Chiwenga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constantine_Chiwenga\"}, {\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirsty Coventry\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Vice President flew int